      "parameters": {
        "color": 6,
        "width": 880,
        "height": 1100,
        "content": "## üîπ SECTION 1: Detect and Sort Issues from Notion\n**Combining**: Schedule Trigger + Notion Database + Field Mapping + Status Routing\n\n## ‚è∞ 1. Schedule Trigger\nüîß **Node Type**: Schedule Trigger (you can use a webhook trigger if you are on Notion paid plan)\n\n## üí¨ Description: Triggers the workflow every X minutes to check for new or updated Notion database pages.\n\n## üìë 2. Get Many Database Pages (Notion)\nüîß **Node Type**: Notion ‚Üí Get All Database Pages\n\n## üìã What it does: Fetches all rows (pages) from a Notion database that represents tasks or feature requests.\n\n‚úèÔ∏è 3. Sort Issues Fields\nüîß **Node Type**: Set\n\n## üìã Goal: Restructures or cleans data fields such as Title, Status, Labels, and Repository.\n\n## üîÄ 4. Switch: Issue Status Decision\nüîß **Node Type**: Switch\n\n## üéØ What it does: Separates logic based on the Status of the Notion item:\n\n**If status is \"To develop\"** ‚Üí proceed to create issue\n\n**Else** ‚Üí send notification to the team"
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "246e38b3-eb3d-47f8-9818-e0c48e9c308f",
      "name": "Sticky Note2",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        1160,
        -1360
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 4,
        "width": 640,
        "height": 760,
        "content": "## üîπ SECTION 2: GitHub Issue Creation (IF \"To develop\")\n**Combining**: GitHub Node + Notion Update\n\n## üêô 5. Create an Issue (GitHub)\nüîß **Node Type**: GitHub ‚Üí Create Issue\n\n## ‚öôÔ∏è What it does: Creates a new issue on the GitHub repo defined in the Notion row.\n\n## üì• Inputs: Uses dynamic fields: Title, Description, Labels, Repository.\n\n## üß© 6. Set Status and Issue URL (Notion Update)\nüîß **Node Type**: Notion ‚Üí Update Database Page\n\n## üß† Role: Updates the status of the issue in Notion to In progress and stores the created GitHub Issue URL."
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7a5f0935-2dc8-4db4-8044-1f261b1820dd",
      "name": "Sticky Note3",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "position": [
        1260,
        -380
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "color": 3,
        "width": 960,
        "height": 1020,
        "content": "## üîπ SECTION 3: Notify Team on Already In-Progress Items (IF NOT \"To develop\")\nCombining: Notion Users + Filtering + Email Grouping + Gmail\n\n## üë• 7. Get Many Users (Notion Users)\nüîß **Node Type**: Notion ‚Üí Get All Users\n\n## üì• What it does: Retrieves the list of team members (to be notified).\n\n## üß† 8. Map Notion Users\nüîß **Node Type**: Set\n\n## üìã Role: Maps and formats data for each user (e.g., Name, Email, Role).\n\n## üßπ 9. Exclude Bot\nüîß **Node Type**: Switch\n\n## üö´ What it does: Excludes automation/bot users (e.g., notifications@noreply).\n\n## üßÆ 10. Group Recipients\nüîß **Node Type**: Aggregate\n\n## üéØ Goal: Collects all user emails into a single array to send one email to all recipients.\n\n## üì¨ 11. Send a Message (Gmail)\nüîß **Node Type**: Gmail ‚Üí Send Email"
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    }
